actions.message: **To create a makeshift pour-over, place your filter on top of the coffee cup. It doesn’t matter whether you have a thick or thin filter, but it does need to be clean. Paper filters are cheap, easy to find and carry. If you don’t have one, use a clean cloth and tie it to a sieve. Once the filter is in follow these steps for an amazing cup of coffee:**
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #1** - Rinse the filter with hot water.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #2** - Measure a tablespoon of coffee for each cup of coffee you want to make.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #3** - Grind your coffee on a medium, sand-like grind.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #4** - Wet the grounds with a little water and wait for at least 30 seconds (longer if your beans are very fresh).
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #5** - Pour half of the remaining water over a 30-second duration.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #6** - Pour the rest of the water in three or four smaller increments.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #7** - Grab the cup/s and open the front door.
actions.name: Send Message

actions.message: **STEP #8** - Pour that shit onto the grass and wait for the grass to eventually die.
